# Restock Workflow Task Completion Log

Updated: 2026-05-14

## 1. Manage Suppliers cards must be expandable and show linked items through a modal

### Completed implementation
- Reworked the Manage Suppliers list so each supplier renders as a semantic `<section>` with a single card-header toggle instead of using the entire supplier row as a nested interactive button.
- Collapsed cards now show only the low-clutter essentials: supplier name, the best available contact, linked-item count, and lead time.
- Expanded cards now show the full supplier detail set: email, phone, minimum order, payment terms, city, address, reorder schedule, schedule notes, supplier notes, and action buttons.
- Added a dedicated **View linked items** button in each expanded supplier card. This button opens the linked-items modal without relying on the collapsed card itself.
- Kept **Link item**, **Edit**, and **Delete** controls visible only when a supplier card is expanded, reducing the visual density of the default list.

### How to verify truthfully
1. Navigate to `/admin/restock/suppliers`.
2. Confirm each supplier appears as a compact collapsed card with minimal supplier details.
3. Click a supplier card header and confirm it expands inline.
4. Confirm the expanded section contains the full supplier details and the action buttons.
5. Click **View linked items** and confirm the linked-items modal opens for that supplier.
6. Inspect the DOM or React console warnings and confirm there is no `<button>` nested inside another `<button>` for supplier cards.
7. Programmatic verification performed: `npx tsc --noEmit --pretty false` and `npm run lint` both passed.

## 2. Supplier linked-items modal must show paginated expandable items with edit controls only after click

### Completed implementation
- Increased supplier linked-items modal pagination to 20 items per page.
- Added a search box to the linked-items modal so users can filter linked supplier items by item name, product id, SKU, notes, or product type.
- Changed modal rows into expandable item cards. Each collapsed item row shows only summary data: name, type, inventory source, SKU, unit cost, and minimum quantity.
- Moved all editable fields and destructive actions behind the expanded item state. Users now click an item row before seeing item name, SKU, unit cost, minimum quantity, notes, Save, and Unlink controls.
- Reset the linked-items modal search, page number, and expanded item whenever a new supplier linked-items modal is opened.

### How to verify truthfully
1. Navigate to `/admin/restock/suppliers`.
2. Expand a supplier with linked items and click **View linked items**.
3. Confirm the modal states that it is showing 20 per page and that pagination controls are present.
4. Confirm linked item cards are collapsed by default and do not show editable form fields initially.
5. Click one linked item and confirm edit fields plus **Save** and **Unlink** appear for only that item.
6. Enter text in the modal search box and confirm the item list and pagination counts filter immediately.
7. Programmatic verification performed: `npx tsc --noEmit --pretty false` and `npm run lint` both passed.

